{"id":6600,"date":"2017-07-24T17:00:36","date_gmt":"2017-07-24T17:00:36","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/?p=6600"},"modified":"2019-07-17T17:31:07","modified_gmt":"2019-07-17T17:31:07","slug":"get-started-developing-with-visual-studio-2015","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/2017\/07\/24\/get-started-developing-with-visual-studio-2015\/","title":{"rendered":"Get Started Developing with Visual Studio"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><a href=\"#Intro\">Introduction<\/a><br \/>\n<a href=\"#Part 1\">\u00a01: Installing Visual Studio<\/a><br \/>\n<a href=\"#Part 2\">\u00a02: Launch Visual Studio IDE<\/a><br \/>\n<a href=\"#Part 3\">\u00a03: Create a New Project<\/a><br \/>\n<a href=\"#Con\">Conclusion<\/a><\/p>\n<hr \/>\n<h2 id=\"Intro\">Introduction<\/h2>\n<p>With the help of <strong><a href=\"https:\/\/www.visualstudio.com\/vs\/older-downloads\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Visual Studio<\/a>\u00a0<\/strong>you can create software, using complete development life cycle, containing planning phase, UI design, coding, testing, debugging, analyzing code quality and performance, deploying to customers, and gathering telemetry on usage.\u00a0 Many applications can be created using <strong>Visual Studio<\/strong> including but not limited to following:<\/p>\n<ol>\n<li>apps and games that run not only on Windows, but also Android and iOS.<\/li>\n<li>websites and web services based on ASP.NET, JQuery, AngularJS, and other popular frameworks<\/li>\n<li>applications for platforms and devices as diverse as Azure, Office, Sharepoint, Hololens, Kinect, and Internet of Things, to name just a few examples<\/li>\n<li>games and graphics-intensive applications for a variety of Windows devices, including Xbox, using DirectX.<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n<h3>For anyone still using <strong>Visual Studio 2015<\/strong> or would like to start with <strong>Visual Studio 2015<\/strong><\/h3>\n<p>I will explain in this article basic installation and set steps.<\/p>\n<p class=\"green\"><span class=\"ion-info\">More Info<\/span>If you prefer to use Mac, see how it looks in <a href=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/2017\/07\/30\/visual-studio-for-mac\/\">Visual Studio for Mac<\/a> post.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3 id=\"Part 1\">Part 1: Installing Visual Studio<\/h3>\n<ol>\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ol>\n<li>You can download <strong>Visual Studio <\/strong> by downloading it from <strong><a href=\"https:\/\/www.visualstudio.com\/downloads\/download-visual-studio-vs.aspx\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Visual Studio Downloads<\/a><\/strong>. If you need any help regarding installation process, you can learn more by visiting <strong><a href=\"https:\/\/msdn.microsoft.com\/en-us\/library\/e2h7fzkw.aspx\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Microsoft Developer Network<\/a><\/strong> website.<\/li>\n<li>Now that you have downloaded the <strong>Visual Studio installer<\/strong>, you can double click on it and start initializing the setup.<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-6606\" src=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/09\/Initialize-installation-3.jpg\" alt=\"initialize-installation\" width=\"1372\" height=\"701\" srcset=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/09\/Initialize-installation-3.jpg 1372w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/09\/Initialize-installation-3-300x153.jpg 300w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/09\/Initialize-installation-3-768x392.jpg 768w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/09\/Initialize-installation-3-1024x523.jpg 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1372px) 100vw, 1372px\" \/><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>3. It shows you the location where the <strong>Visual Studio IDE<\/strong> is going to be installed and the different types of installs available. Let&#8217;s start with the <strong>default install<\/strong> option that is pre-selected. You can also select <strong>custom install<\/strong>. <strong>A custom install<\/strong> will show you a list of feature that you can include in your install.<\/p>\n<p>4. Click on<strong> Install<\/strong>. Installing <strong>Visual Studio<\/strong> might take a while.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-6607\" src=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/09\/visual-studio-type-of-installation-default.jpg\" alt=\"visual-studio-type-of-installation-default\" width=\"315\" height=\"436\" srcset=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/09\/visual-studio-type-of-installation-default.jpg 315w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/09\/visual-studio-type-of-installation-default-217x300.jpg 217w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 315px) 100vw, 315px\" \/><\/p>\n<p class=\"gray\">You can see <strong><a href=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/watch?v=hDujfznIZFE\">this video<\/a><\/strong>, if you would like to find more information about how to install Visual Studio 2017 and point to some tricky components. See which Workloads needs to be installed and which Individual Components needs to be selected additionally. See how to install another Edition of Visual Studio and just put different nickname in order to distinguish installed editions.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3 id=\"Part 2\">Part 2: Launch Visual Studio IDE<\/h3>\n<p>1. After Installing <strong>Visual Studio<\/strong> and once your computer has restarted, you can now launch <strong>Visual Studio IDE<\/strong> for the very first time. Type <strong>visual studio<\/strong> into your search menu and then click on it.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-6608\" src=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/09\/Type-visual-studio-in-search-menu.jpg\" alt=\"type-visual-studio-in-search-menu\" width=\"864\" height=\"387\" srcset=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/09\/Type-visual-studio-in-search-menu.jpg 864w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/09\/Type-visual-studio-in-search-menu-300x134.jpg 300w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/09\/Type-visual-studio-in-search-menu-768x344.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 864px) 100vw, 864px\" \/><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>2. You need to sign in with your <strong>outlook account<\/strong>. Type in your email address and password.<\/p>\n<p>3. Click on Sign in.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-6609\" src=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/09\/Sign-in-to-outlook-account.jpg\" alt=\"sign-in-to-outlook-account\" width=\"315\" height=\"385\" srcset=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/09\/Sign-in-to-outlook-account.jpg 315w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/09\/Sign-in-to-outlook-account-245x300.jpg 245w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 315px) 100vw, 315px\" \/><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>4. Once you have signed in, you will be presented with your <strong>full name<\/strong>, <strong>contact email<\/strong>, <strong>region<\/strong> and the <strong>option to create a team service site<\/strong>. You can do whatever as per your needs but for now click on <strong>Continue<\/strong>.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-6610\" src=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/09\/contact-information.jpg\" alt=\"contact-information\" width=\"318\" height=\"387\" srcset=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/09\/contact-information.jpg 318w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/09\/contact-information-247x300.jpg 247w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 318px) 100vw, 318px\" \/><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3>5. Let&#8217;s start with the default theme and click on <strong>Start Visual Studio<\/strong>.<\/h3>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-6611\" src=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/09\/visual-studio-environment.jpg\" alt=\"visual-studio-environment\" width=\"316\" height=\"385\" srcset=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/09\/visual-studio-environment.jpg 316w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/09\/visual-studio-environment-246x300.jpg 246w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 316px) 100vw, 316px\" \/><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p><strong>6. Visual Studio<\/strong> has got a <strong>start up page<\/strong> made up of how to start a project by starting a new project, opening an existing project or opening it from source control.<\/p>\n<p>7 . In the middle of the page, there is <strong>Discover Visual Studio Community resources<\/strong>. This consists bunch of resources that could help you get started.<\/p>\n<p>8. To the right, we have a <strong>solution explorer<\/strong>.<\/p>\n<p>9. At the bottom of the page, there is an <strong>output window<\/strong>.<\/p>\n<p>10. In the top right corner, there is <strong>notification icon<\/strong>, <strong>send feedback icon<\/strong> and the <strong>quick launch search box<\/strong>. <strong>Notification<\/strong> provides you with any extension or product updates.<\/p>\n<p><strong>11.Feedback<\/strong> is a great way of telling how we are doing.<\/p>\n<p><strong>12. Quick launch<\/strong> is a fast way to access menus and features in Visual Studio.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-6627\" src=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/09\/visual-studio-type-of-installation-default-1.jpg\" alt=\"visual-studio-type-of-installation-default\" width=\"861\" height=\"442\" srcset=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/09\/visual-studio-type-of-insta